prepare the necessary Adjusting Journal Entry to correct the overstatement of the Advances for Payroll Account and set up the receivable from each of the 15 Barangays;
demand from the Punong Barangays the issuance of an Official Receipt of the funds transferred;
demand from the Punong Barangays the Submission of the Liquidation Report, Purchase Orders/Contracts and required supporting documents evidencing the disbursement of the funds received to the Municipal Accounting Office; and
refrain or desist from drawing Cash Advances thru payroll in granting Financial Assistance which are not essentially for the payment of services rendered in an attempt to circumvent COA Rules and Regulations.

We recommended that the Management to:

Use the modified accrual method of accounting for its Real Property
taxes and Special Education Taxes as prescribed for in the NGAS Manual for LGUs, Volume 1 and IPSAS 23;

Direct the Municipal Treasurer to prepare a certified list of tax payers and the corresponding amount due and collectible for the calendar year as basis of the Municipal Accountant in setting up the correct Real Property Tax / Special Education Tax receivables;

Prepare the necessary adjusting journal entry for the Real Property Tax Receivable and Special Education Tax Receivable balances that were closed against the Government Equity account.

